    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but just thinking about the tech itself... even if they don't have 'emotions', they do have microphones for voice commands and cameras for the apps, right? and they're all on the same wifi. if someone wanted to use the metadata from those sensors to track patterns, wouldn't that be a pretty simple way to monitor someone without them knowing? like, it wouldn't need to be 'conscious', just data scraping.",
